17
00:00:12,047 --> 00:00:12,164
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,165 --> 00:00:15,165
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,189 --> 00:00:19,357
<i>A terrorist threat!</i>

20
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:22,360
<i>Moralo Eval,
mastermind of a Separatist plot</i>

21
00:00:22,443 --> 00:00:26,572
<i>to kidnap Chancellor Palpatine,
has been captured by Republic forces!</i>

22
00:00:26,697 --> 00:00:29,283
<i>But even with the criminal behind bars,</i>

23
00:00:29,325 --> 00:00:31,786
<i>rumors swirl in
the underworld of Coruscant</i>

24
00:00:31,827 --> 00:00:35,164
<i>that Moralo's plot has already
been set in motion...</i>

25
00:00:35,248 --> 00:00:39,085
<i>With precious time running out,
the Jedi Council hatches their own plot</i>

26
00:00:39,126 --> 00:00:41,337
<i>to keep the Chancellor safe.</i>

27
00:00:43,798 --> 00:00:45,591
So what's the big rush?

28
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:47,969
The Jedi Council has called
an emergency meeting.

29
00:00:48,928 --> 00:00:50,346
I can see it now.

30
00:00:50,429 --> 00:00:52,640
Another long, boring debate.

31
00:00:58,646 --> 00:01:01,315
Would you rather they call you in
to train younglings?

32
00:01:01,816 --> 00:01:03,317
Are you crazy?

33
00:01:11,742 --> 00:01:13,828
Any idea where that shot came from?

34
00:01:15,037 --> 00:01:17,248
A sniper. I see him up there!

35
00:01:17,873 --> 00:01:19,208
All right, here's the plan.

36
00:01:19,292 --> 00:01:21,002
Anakin, you flank him on the right.

37
00:01:21,043 --> 00:01:22,837
Ahsoka, you cover the lower streets.

38
00:01:23,045 --> 00:01:24,672
I'm going after him.

39
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:01,751
I lost him!

40
00:02:01,876 --> 00:02:03,753
<i>Obi-Wan, do you have anything?</i>

41
00:02:17,558 --> 00:02:19,894
-Obi-Wan !
-I got him, go!

42
00:02:45,419 --> 00:02:46,754
How is he?

43
00:02:49,465 --> 00:02:51,467
Obi-Wan. Obi-Wan.

44
00:02:52,551 --> 00:02:53,886
Obi-Wan!

45
00:03:14,699 --> 00:03:16,409
I'm worried about Anakin.

46
00:03:16,450 --> 00:03:19,036
He hasn't said a word since it happened.

47
00:03:45,771 --> 00:03:46,772
Wow.

48
00:03:47,189 --> 00:03:49,567
I want to check his midi-chlorian count.

49
00:03:49,650 --> 00:03:51,819
What's your pleasure?

50
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:54,113
Shot of your finest.

51
00:03:58,242 --> 00:04:00,911
So what's the big deal?

52
00:04:01,829 --> 00:04:03,122
I'm celebrating.

53
00:04:03,164 --> 00:04:06,375
The death of a Jedi.

54
00:04:07,334 --> 00:04:09,837
I killed Obi-Wan Kenobi!

55
00:04:13,841 --> 00:04:15,843
Having second thoughts, Master Yoda?

56
00:04:16,093 --> 00:04:19,430
Hmm, heading down a dark path, we are.

57
00:04:20,389 --> 00:04:21,766
We talked about this.

58
00:04:21,849 --> 00:04:24,560
Killing a Jedi was the best move we had.

59
00:04:25,728 --> 00:04:26,812
Hmm.

60
00:04:38,073 --> 00:04:40,075
So, how was my funeral?

61
00:04:40,284 --> 00:04:43,078
A better performance than you,
your corpse gave.

62
00:04:43,579 --> 00:04:44,789
Whatever do you mean?

63
00:04:44,872 --> 00:04:46,457
I fell from the top of a building.

64
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,292
I could have killed myself.

65
00:04:48,584 --> 00:04:50,544
Survived worse, you have.

66
00:04:50,878 --> 00:04:52,922
Young Skywalker knows this.

67
00:04:53,631 --> 00:04:56,175
I took the vitals suppressor as instructed.

68
00:04:56,217 --> 00:04:58,552
I was dead to the world
when Anakin moved my body.

69
00:04:58,719 --> 00:05:00,679
There's no way he could know I was alive.

70
00:05:01,096 --> 00:05:02,348
Not know.

71
00:05:02,389 --> 00:05:05,726
But sense, he will,
that something is not right.

72
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:08,687
Keeping Anakin on the outside was critical.

73
00:05:08,729 --> 00:05:10,523
Everyone knows how close we are.

74
00:05:10,564 --> 00:05:13,108
It was his reaction that sold the sniper.

75
00:05:13,192 --> 00:05:14,318
I'm sure of it.

76
00:05:14,443 --> 00:05:16,237
What's done is done.

77
00:05:16,403 --> 00:05:18,531
We need to get
your transformation underway.

78
00:05:18,906 --> 00:05:21,033
Well, time for a shave!

79
00:05:22,868 --> 00:05:24,537
Tell me about my target.

80
00:05:24,912 --> 00:05:26,997
His name is Moralo Eval.

81
00:05:27,081 --> 00:05:28,749
Works directly for Count Dooku.

82
00:05:29,208 --> 00:05:31,710
Rumor is their plot will be hatched
in three revolutions

83
00:05:31,794 --> 00:05:33,420
at the festival on Naboo.

84
00:05:33,504 --> 00:05:39,093
We tried to make a deal with Moralo
for more details, but he was uncooperative.

85
00:05:39,844 --> 00:05:42,888
Any details that might help me gain
his trust while in prison?

86
00:05:43,264 --> 00:05:45,724
Eval killed his mother
when he was only a boy.

87
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:48,769
Told the authorities he did it
because he was bored.

88
00:05:49,812 --> 00:05:51,605
Hmm, I'll try not to bore him.

89
00:05:51,647 --> 00:05:53,899
Not a game is this, Obi-Wan.

90
00:05:53,941 --> 00:05:56,277
The risks, great they are.

91
00:05:56,777 --> 00:05:58,737
Yes, and so are the rewards.

92
00:05:58,946 --> 00:06:01,657
Besides preventing Eval
from abducting the Chancellor,

93
00:06:01,740 --> 00:06:05,035
he could lead us to Grievous,
and possibly Dooku himself.

94
00:06:05,286 --> 00:06:07,913
Facial transformation program loaded.

95
00:06:08,831 --> 00:06:12,793
I take it there's no way to have
the Chancellor pull out of the festival?

96
00:06:13,294 --> 00:06:16,130
No. See it as a sign of weakness, he would.

97
00:06:16,964 --> 00:06:19,633
Sign of weakness.
Wouldn't want that.

98
00:06:28,309 --> 00:06:30,311
Transformation initiated.

99
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:44,783
This cant in a is a bust.

100
00:06:44,825 --> 00:06:46,327
Do you want to go to the next one?

101
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:48,120
Rako Hardeen?

102
00:06:48,871 --> 00:06:50,623
Who wants to know?

103
00:06:50,998 --> 00:06:52,875
Your employer has your payment.

104
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:54,710
Please follow me.

105
00:06:56,128 --> 00:06:57,713
Round for the house!

106
00:06:59,882 --> 00:07:01,383
- Yes!
- Oh, yeah!

107
00:07:03,177 --> 00:07:04,637
This way.

108
00:07:07,014 --> 00:07:09,016
Inside if you please.

109
00:07:13,854 --> 00:07:15,397
Well done, Mr. Hardeen.

110
00:07:15,481 --> 00:07:18,317
You did precisely the job we hired you for.

111
00:07:18,359 --> 00:07:19,902
We have your credits right here.

112
00:07:19,985 --> 00:07:22,905
But first we need one more thing...

113
00:07:27,534 --> 00:07:28,827
Your clothes.

114
00:07:29,119 --> 00:07:30,371
What the...

115
00:07:43,217 --> 00:07:44,551
I still don't understand.

116
00:07:44,635 --> 00:07:47,054
Did Master Yoda say how they found
the sniper?

117
00:07:47,137 --> 00:07:48,222
Who cares.

118
00:07:48,305 --> 00:07:50,307
All that matters is they did.

119
00:07:56,730 --> 00:08:01,735
So I took off in my speeder,
and then I got a ride here. That's it.

120
00:08:01,902 --> 00:08:03,445
Keep talking. Into this.

121
00:08:04,697 --> 00:08:05,906
This is stupid!

122
00:08:05,948 --> 00:08:08,075
Confessing to a murder I didn't even do!

123
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:10,077
Oh, but you did...

124
00:08:10,119 --> 00:08:12,871
For all intents and purposes,
Obi-Wan Kenobi is dead.

125
00:08:13,163 --> 00:08:15,582
And that certainly was your intention.

126
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:16,917
How do I look?

127
00:08:17,126 --> 00:08:18,335
Like a criminal.

128
00:08:18,419 --> 00:08:20,838
Should buy you all the credibility
you need in prison.

129
00:08:21,922 --> 00:08:24,258
Look, I don't know what you guys
are up to, but...

130
00:08:24,299 --> 00:08:25,634
Do we have enough recording?

131
00:08:25,718 --> 00:08:27,136
I believe so.

132
00:08:27,636 --> 00:08:30,764
Which means you can go to sleep now.

133
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:35,602
So how does this vocal emulator work?

134
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:41,066
Well, you swallow it.

135
00:08:43,193 --> 00:08:45,446
I was afraid you'd say that.

136
00:08:51,368 --> 00:08:53,328
What an odd sensation.

137
00:08:54,288 --> 00:08:56,665
It will take some getting used to.

138
00:08:57,458 --> 00:08:59,543
That's a luxury you don't have.

139
00:09:00,085 --> 00:09:02,046
I hope this works.

140
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,227
Where is Rako Hardeen?

141
00:09:18,562 --> 00:09:20,147
Back room.

142
00:09:29,323 --> 00:09:30,407
Is he dead?

143
00:09:30,491 --> 00:09:32,117
He's about to be.

144
00:09:35,412 --> 00:09:39,041
A Jedi? I already killed a Jedi today.

145
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,626
Let me sleep.

146
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:43,170
He's not dead. He's drunk.

147
00:09:43,796 --> 00:09:45,714
Get up, you filth!

148
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:50,177
If it was up to me I would kill you
right here!

149
00:09:50,844 --> 00:09:55,933
But lucky for you, the man you
murdered would rather see you rot in jail.

150
00:09:59,895 --> 00:10:03,816
Now, let's go, you coward,
before I change my mind.

151
00:10:12,324 --> 00:10:14,201
You should be expecting this scum.

152
00:10:15,035 --> 00:10:16,286
Yes, sir.

153
00:10:16,411 --> 00:10:17,955
Let me know if he's any trouble.

154
00:10:18,038 --> 00:10:19,998
I'd be happy to straighten him out.

155
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:49,069
That's him!

156
00:10:49,153 --> 00:10:50,737
Kenobi's killer!

157
00:10:52,072 --> 00:10:53,323
Rako Hardeen.

158
00:10:53,407 --> 00:10:55,284
He doesn't look so tough.

159
00:10:55,576 --> 00:10:57,077
He killed a Jedi.

160
00:11:08,589 --> 00:11:11,633
That's him? That's the Jedi killer?

161
00:11:12,259 --> 00:11:14,261
He doesn't look so tough.

162
00:11:16,430 --> 00:11:18,682
You don't look so tough to me.

163
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:21,810
This food tastes terrible.

164
00:11:27,941 --> 00:11:29,943
Maybe you'd taste better.

165
00:11:31,195 --> 00:11:33,071
Hey, what's going on down there?

166
00:11:33,906 --> 00:11:36,283
Sorry, just playing with my food.

167
00:11:38,118 --> 00:11:39,578
You're crazy!

168
00:11:51,423 --> 00:11:52,966
Rako Hardeen.

169
00:11:53,383 --> 00:11:56,220
Your reputation precedes you.

170
00:11:56,970 --> 00:12:00,766
I'm curious, when you killed that Jedi,

171
00:12:01,016 --> 00:12:04,019
was it for money or revenge?

172
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:07,272
I don't know. Guess I was bored.

173
00:12:10,776 --> 00:12:12,402
Try the sauce.

174
00:12:12,653 --> 00:12:15,656
It makes that slop almost tolerable.

175
00:12:16,323 --> 00:12:19,701
I'll be seeing you, Mr. Hardeen.

176
00:12:36,969 --> 00:12:40,347
Here you go, Hardeen. Home, sweet home.

177
00:12:45,018 --> 00:12:46,520
What a coincidence.

178
00:12:46,979 --> 00:12:48,522
No coincidence.

179
00:12:48,981 --> 00:12:51,525
I am Moralo Eval,

180
00:12:51,608 --> 00:12:54,695
and I have great influence here.

181
00:12:54,861 --> 00:12:56,196
What do you want from me?

182
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:58,532
A man like you...

183
00:12:58,615 --> 00:13:01,034
There's bigger game than Jedi,

184
00:13:01,493 --> 00:13:03,829
if you've got the guts.

185
00:13:05,038 --> 00:13:06,540
I'm listening.

186
00:13:07,207 --> 00:13:09,793
It's a brilliant plan if I do say so.

187
00:13:09,876 --> 00:13:12,546
And it involves the Chancellor.

188
00:13:14,214 --> 00:13:17,509
If I'm breaking out this goon along with us,

189
00:13:17,843 --> 00:13:19,386
it'll cost you.

190
00:13:19,511 --> 00:13:21,054
Double my rate.

191
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:27,227
Rako Hardeen, meet Cad Bane.

192
00:13:27,561 --> 00:13:29,438
Who you calling a goon?

193
00:13:30,230 --> 00:13:34,901
Any imbecile can kill a Jedi
with a lousy sniper blast.

194
00:13:34,985 --> 00:13:36,903
You want my respect?

195
00:13:38,822 --> 00:13:41,408
You do it face-to-face.

196
00:13:42,451 --> 00:13:44,745
Who said I want your respect?

197
00:13:45,579 --> 00:13:49,166
Make that triple my rate.

198
00:13:49,249 --> 00:13:51,585
Oh, what a shame.

199
00:13:51,668 --> 00:13:55,464
Seems this cell isn't big enough for
the three of us.

200
00:13:55,589 --> 00:13:56,757
Guard!

201
00:13:58,884 --> 00:14:01,803
It's been a pleasure chatting
with you, Hardeen.

202
00:14:02,012 --> 00:14:05,766
But you will forget everything you
heard in here,

203
00:14:06,266 --> 00:14:10,604
or Moralo Eval will have you slaughtered.

204
00:14:28,914 --> 00:14:30,707
We were just leaving.

205
00:14:48,266 --> 00:14:49,684
<i>This is Ben.</i>

206
00:14:49,893 --> 00:14:52,687
<i>I found the transmitter,
but I shall have to make this short.</i>

207
00:14:53,063 --> 00:14:54,272
<i>We have a problem.</i>

208
00:14:54,981 --> 00:14:56,566
I made contact with Eval.

209
00:14:56,650 --> 00:15:00,612
He nearly divulged his kidnap plot,
but Cad Bane stopped him.

210
00:15:00,904 --> 00:15:04,366
Cad Bane? We had no intel they were
in league together.

211
00:15:05,075 --> 00:15:07,911
<i>It appears Eval's hired Bane
to break him out of prison,</i>

212
00:15:07,994 --> 00:15:10,539
<i>and the way they were talking,
it's imminent.</i>

213
00:15:10,872 --> 00:15:14,960
Foolish we were, to believe Bane's
capture was without purpose.

214
00:15:15,502 --> 00:15:18,171
<i>Yes. Yes, but we can make
this work for us.</i>

215
00:15:18,338 --> 00:15:21,466
<i>If they do try to escape,
I won't let them out of my sight.</i>

216
00:15:21,591 --> 00:15:24,678
<i>No doubt he shall lead us
to some answers about the plot</i>

217
00:15:24,719 --> 00:15:26,346
<i>and possibly to his superiors.</i>

218
00:15:26,388 --> 00:15:27,848
Good idea, Obi-Wan.

219
00:15:27,931 --> 00:15:30,058
Just don't blow your cover.

220
00:15:30,183 --> 00:15:32,436
It could take a while
to extract you from prison.

221
00:15:33,311 --> 00:15:34,521
Not to worry.

222
00:15:34,604 --> 00:15:36,857
I'm starting to enjoy playing the villain.

223
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,024
Gotta go!

224
00:15:48,452 --> 00:15:49,995
Hey, Hardeen!

225
00:15:52,581 --> 00:15:53,832
You owe me something.

226
00:15:53,915 --> 00:15:55,208
Oh, do I?

227
00:15:55,584 --> 00:15:57,294
You don't even remember me?

228
00:15:57,377 --> 00:15:59,212
That's very insulting.

229
00:15:59,671 --> 00:16:01,590
Look, kid, I don't want any trouble.

230
00:16:03,175 --> 00:16:05,886
You stole a bounty from me,
and I want an apology!

231
00:16:06,052 --> 00:16:08,388
Kill him, Hardeen, like the Jedi!

232
00:16:08,597 --> 00:16:11,016
What's wrong, Hardeen?
Lose your spine?

233
00:16:11,057 --> 00:16:13,059
- You don't want to do this.
- Kill him!

234
00:16:16,771 --> 00:16:18,273
Oh, yes, I do.

235
00:16:26,531 --> 00:16:28,241
I warned you.

236
00:16:28,909 --> 00:16:30,035
All right, all right, that's it!

237
00:16:30,076 --> 00:16:31,244
Fight's over!

238
00:16:32,287 --> 00:16:33,872
No, it ain't!

239
00:16:35,582 --> 00:16:40,170
You got a problem with Boba,
you got a problem with me!

240
00:16:44,716 --> 00:16:46,593
All right, that's enough, big fella!

241
00:16:49,262 --> 00:16:50,889
-Fight!
-Let's get them!

242
00:16:51,765 --> 00:16:52,933
Let's get them!

243
00:16:53,058 --> 00:16:54,976
- Riot!
- Get the guards!

244
00:16:55,101 --> 00:16:56,311
- Get 'em !
- Yeah!

245
00:16:56,853 --> 00:16:58,939
We need reinforcements in here. Now!

246
00:16:59,272 --> 00:17:00,982
Kill the guards!

247
00:17:03,276 --> 00:17:04,903
Riot! Riot!

248
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,615
What do we do?

249
00:17:08,698 --> 00:17:10,700
Part of my plan.

250
00:17:10,992 --> 00:17:13,703
Paid off the kid to create a diversion.

251
00:17:19,876 --> 00:17:20,961
Let's go.

252
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:36,476
<i>Facility on lockdown. Facility on lockdown.</i>

253
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,562
<i>Facility on lockdown.</i>

254
00:17:38,645 --> 00:17:39,688
Turn your weapons off stun!

255
00:17:39,771 --> 00:17:41,523
Kill the prisoners if you have to!

256
00:17:45,026 --> 00:17:46,653
Hey, wait for me.

257
00:17:46,903 --> 00:17:49,072
No one invited you.

258
00:17:49,489 --> 00:17:53,159
He killed a Jedi. He could be helpful.

259
00:17:54,828 --> 00:17:57,372
Fine. We're wasting time.

260
00:18:02,711 --> 00:18:06,506
Uh, I'm telling you,
it's gonna be a long night.

261
00:18:13,763 --> 00:18:15,682
This is our way out of here.

262
00:18:16,391 --> 00:18:20,020
The morgue? This is your brilliant plan?

263
00:18:20,437 --> 00:18:23,982
Not the first time I've broken out
of this stink hole.

264
00:18:34,492 --> 00:18:36,286
The lock has changed.

265
00:18:37,037 --> 00:18:38,663
Your plan has failed.

266
00:18:38,705 --> 00:18:40,707
Shut up! Let me think.

267
00:18:43,418 --> 00:18:46,212
I can get us inside.
I'll re-wire the access port on this door.

268
00:18:46,296 --> 00:18:48,798
It'll take some time,
so warn me if anyone comes.

269
00:18:49,049 --> 00:18:50,550
Make it quick.

270
00:19:01,686 --> 00:19:02,687
We're in!

271
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,070
All the riot casualties are sent
to the crematorium.

272
00:19:10,737 --> 00:19:12,489
From there it's an easy escape.

273
00:19:12,572 --> 00:19:13,907
Another night,
another riot.

274
00:19:13,948 --> 00:19:15,492
The guards are coming back.

275
00:19:15,575 --> 00:19:16,868
You said it, partner.

276
00:19:19,621 --> 00:19:22,290
I'll take blasting clankers any day
over this.

277
00:19:22,374 --> 00:19:25,126
Yeah, me too, give me droids over
this prison scum.

278
00:19:25,794 --> 00:19:28,672
After what just happened up there,
we'll need more room in here.

279
00:19:29,506 --> 00:19:30,840
You can say that again.

280
00:19:30,924 --> 00:19:33,051
Here, I'll send these
to the cremation center.

281
00:19:47,607 --> 00:19:50,944
Hey, wait, it looks like a couple
of them are showing vital signs.

282
00:19:51,194 --> 00:19:52,737
All right, I'll check it out.

283
00:20:11,506 --> 00:20:12,799
What's the matter with you?

284
00:20:12,966 --> 00:20:14,509
My blaster jammed.

285
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,596
Let's go!

286
00:21:03,308 --> 00:21:06,019
Soon as we're off Coruscant, we're safe.

287
00:21:18,156 --> 00:21:21,534
That's for hesitating during the escape.

288
00:21:22,035 --> 00:21:24,412
If it wasn't for me,
we'd still be stuck in there.

289
00:21:24,954 --> 00:21:28,416
Yeah, funny how that worked out.

290
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:39,803
Hey, my ship! Come back here!

291
00:21:43,056 --> 00:21:45,391
You did well in there, Hardeen.

292
00:21:45,809 --> 00:21:49,562
Maybe there's a place for you
in my plans after all.

293
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:52,065
I'm listening.

294
00:21:52,089 --> 00:21:57,089
http://hiqve.com/

